de.wwu.muggl.symbolic.searchAlgorithms.choice.conditionalJump
Class ConditionalJumpChoicePoint

java.lang.Object
  de.wwu.muggl.symbolic.searchAlgorithms.choice.conditionalJump.ConditionalJumpChoicePoint
All Implemented Interfaces:
ChoicePoint
Direct Known Subclasses:
ConditionalJumpChoicePointDepthFirst
public abstract class ConditionalJumpChoicePoint
extends java.lang.Object
implements ChoicePoint

A ConditionalJumpChoicePoint is generated whenever a conditional jump statement is reached. Conditional jumps branch the execution tree, leaving two possibilities: Continue at the next instruction in the program flow, or jump to another instruction. To execute a program symbolically, ChoicePoints are set during execution. By using a search algorithm ChoicePoints can be used to track back in the program flow and visit alternative branches in the execution tree. This does not only safe computation time, but enables the effective visiting of different branches at all, since ChoicePoints safe information about what branch has already been visited.

Search algorithms usually extend this class in order to have choice points that offer the functionality needed by them.
